At first, I really liked this app and found it fun to use. Unfortunately, three days after use it has now started flagging a wrong note immediately after each correct one. Problem still occurs after reinstallation of the app. I now have to set it to ignore errors which is not good for tracking my note accuracy. For a paid app this should not happen. If it was fixed, I would give it 5 stars. *Update: Dev replied - now works with sound effects disabled to prevent reverb in room. 5 stars given. :-)
replyContent: Hi Paul, I actually do have an update in the works with a revamped audio detection engine, but in the meantime: this issue is generally caused by the app's sound effects reverberating in the room you're in, and being picked up again by the microphone. Try turning the volume down (or even off) and this issue should go away. Hope that helps! -Thomas

replyContent: Hi Georgia, thanks for updating your rating! I investigated the "high A issue" and realised the correct "ping" sound was in fact a high A pitch and was sometimes itself triggering the "correct" response - now fixed! I've also added a 5-second penalty for wrong notes, so your kids will no longer be able to get 3 stars if they make errors! Enjoy! :)

replyContent: Hi Naftali. The new version uses the camera to scan QR codes of custom levels created in the app. In Android 6.0 and up it only requests that permission when you first access that feature. The Level Designer also lets you put in repetitions as you've requested. Real tunes would change what the app is trying to do, but I thank you for your thoughts!
